 <h2><u>Bangle of Disease</u></h2><br><br>This quest results in this bracer:<br><br><img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/danapics/BangleofDiseaseWarding.gif"><br><br><br>Ok, so its not fantastic, but the effect is an instaclick (click from inventory) <b>40 Disease Resist</b> that you can cast on others. Making it a severely useful item!<br><br>That means that one person could potentially keep a group in instaclickies, and give an entire raid +40 DR.<br><br><br>Whats more, the item acts as a key to the <a href="zones.php3?zone=decay">Crypt of Decay</a> for those without the flag. Sounds good right? Now all you need to do is get it.<br><br><br>To get it, you need to loot the flesh of the following four named flys: <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11642">A Generian Larva</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11084">A Harrior Larva</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=12974">A Scaevian Larva</a> and <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10383">A Sengian Larva</a>. These are rare spawns, and will occasionally spawn in place of the similarily named "larvae" (the named are "larva"). So kill the placeholders until you get the mob you need. Something worth thinking about when <a href='index2.php3?page=podh'>Soloing the Plane of Disease</a>.<br><br>Once you have the four flesh, hand them in to a wandering Ogre named <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10448">Grimror Plaguebringer</a> to get your bracer.<br><br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(163); return false;'>Plane of Disease (PoD) mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(163); return false;'>Plane of Disease (PoD) quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/planes/planeofdiseasemap.html'>Plane of Disease (PoD) Map</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>The 4 named larva have place holders.  The (Malarian Larva)-->(Harrion larva). The Malarian Larva spawns near the flys near the zone in and water with island.  (Planarian Larva)-->(Generian & Sengian Larva).  The Planarian is the place holder for both of these two larva.  The Planarian spawns and roams around on the dirt north of the fly pools, to the east of the castle.  (Tetse Pupa)-->(Scaevian Larva) Note that I said Pupa, not Pupal.  The Tetse Pupal is not a place holder, just like the Larvae are not.  The Tetse Pupa spawns all the way north in Plane of disease near all the buidings with the rats and other mobs in them.  None of the Larva/Larvae/Pupa/Pupal/goo/rats summon.  Some flys do summon, the Malarian I think.  Also, watch out for the spiders, the spiderlings are necro's, and the Arachnae Terranis can complete heal and does often.  The spiderlings are a pretty easy solo with a buffed pet, but the Terranis take alot of mana to kill because of the stupid CH.  I finished my bangle while soloing in this zone, it was very easy to solo all the mobs and get my bangle and I got around 1 AA in 2 hours exp while doing it. <br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Harrion:
- PH are malarian larva found near the fly camps (hang right from GY). What a pain in the ass this one was. Just kill all the PH's on the 2 islands but trick is not to get adds from the flies and swamp rats. Harmony and sometimes pacify works on em. Once all done, pull larva and wait for Harrion to pop.  

Generian / Sengian:
- PH for Generian are planarian larva found near the middle of zone. PH for Sengian are tachnian caterpillars left from the bone entrance of the castle. Suggest you hang around at half way point btw the NW corner and bone entrance and pull. Remember it's LARVA not larvae as PH's.

Scaevian:
- PH for Scaevian are tsetian pupa's (not PUPAL's). Just wait near the NW corner for PH and kill em all until scaevian pops. To kill time while no PH's are up pull some pulsing's as well (be careful to harmony / pacify or you get add city (there is always 4 pulsings in one dome) <br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Harmony? mages cannot use harmony, why include this post in a mage forum.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Quote: "Harmony? mages cannot use harmony, why include this post in a mage forum".

Since when does a strategy to complete a quest have to consist of a soloist mentality? Many quests require additional players or groups to complete.  <br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>my mage can harmony<br><br><i><b>Svfire of Rallos Zek</b> says:</i><br>I swear you guys are idiots..
